---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { highlightKai } from '../../lib/highlight';
import { links } from '../../lib/links';

const helloSnippet = `fn main() {
  println("hello, kaikai")
}`;
const helloHtml = await highlightKai(helloSnippet);
---

<Base title="Get started · kaikai" lang="en">
  <article class="get-started-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header>
        <p class="eyebrow">Get started</p>
        <h1>Installing kaikai</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          The command-line tool is called <code>kai</code>. The
          recommended path is the official installer; Homebrew also
          works, and you can build from source if you want to change
          the compiler itself.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section>
        <h2>Official installer &middot; macOS (Apple Silicon)</h2>
        <p>
          A rustup-style installer with no dependencies:
        </p>
<pre><code>curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kaikailang-org/kaikai/main/install.sh | sh</code></pre>
        <p>
          It downloads the latest release, verifies its SHA-256,
          installs it under <code>~/.kaikai/</code> and adds
          <code>~/.kaikai/bin</code> to your <code>PATH</code>. Verify
          the install:
        </p>
<pre><code>kai --version</code></pre>
        <p>
          The binary is self-contained: LLVM is statically linked, and
          it compiles to native code with no <code>clang</code> or
          external toolchain. To update later:
        </p>
<pre><code>kai upgrade</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Homebrew</h2>
        <p>
          The official distribution also lives in its own tap.
        </p>
<pre><code>brew install kaikailang-org/kaikai/kaikai</code></pre>
        <p>
          On a Homebrew install, updates go through
          <code>brew upgrade kaikai</code>, not <code>kai upgrade</code>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>From source</h2>
        <p>
          You only need this to change the compiler itself, or on
          platforms the installer does not ship binaries for yet
          (prebuilts today are macOS on Apple Silicon). It requires a
          <code>cc</code> and the LLVM development headers (located via
          <code>llvm-config</code>):
        </p>
<pre><code>git clone {links.github.kaikai}
cd kaikai
make all</code></pre>
        <p>
          The bootstrap regenerates the compiler from nothing but a C
          compiler: stage 0 (C) builds <code>kaic0</code>, which
          compiles the minimal compiler <code>kaic1</code>, which
          compiles the full self-hosted compiler.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your first program</h2>
        <p>Save this as <code>hello.kai</code>:</p>
        <div class="code-block" set:html={helloHtml} />
        <p>Then run it:</p>
<pre><code>kai run hello.kai
# hello, kaikai</code></pre>
        <p>To produce a native binary instead of running directly:</p>
<pre><code>kai build hello.kai -o hello
./hello</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What's next</h2>
        <ul class="nextsteps">
          <li>
            Browse the <a href="/en/examples">examples</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            Read the <a href="/en/book">book</a> for the long-form
            walkthrough of the language with real programs.
          </li>
          <li>
            Visit the <a href={links.github.kaikai} rel="noopener">GitHub
            repo</a> and open an issue if something seems off.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .get-started-page {
    padding-block: var(--space-16) var(--space-12);
  }
  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .get-started-page header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }
  .lead {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  section {
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
    max-width: 70ch;
  }
  section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  section p {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  section pre {
    margin-block: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
  }
  .code-block :global(pre.shiki) {
    background: var(--code-bg) !important;
    margin-block: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
  }
  .nextsteps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .nextsteps li::before {
    content: "›";
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-right: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
